abstract: Egypt’s temporary military rulers, in a news conference, deliver a sweeping defense of their tenure, saying they are committed to handing over power to a civil authority by the end of June, and denying any role in clashes the day before that left at least 11 people dead in Cairo.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and MAYY EL SHEIKH

lead_paragraph: The generals also defended their tenure, and said they were “committed” to handing over power to a civil authority by the end of June.
